{"id":"project-LICHEN-vh51","title":"API contract: out_id _Nonnull annotation violated","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_interface/include/lichen/app_interface/app_interface.h:220
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_interface/app_interface.c:86,107

The header declares out_id as _Nonnull:
  int lichen_app_interface_register_sink(
      const struct lichen_app_interface_sink *_Nonnull sink, uint8_t *_Nonnull out_id);

But the implementation treats it as nullable (lines 86-88, 107-108):
  if (out_id != NULL) {
      *out_id = i;
  }

This violates the API contract. Either:
1. Remove the _Nonnull annotation if NULL is intentionally allowed
2. Remove the NULL checks and crash if NULL is passed (consistent with annotation)

Static analyzers and callers relying on nullability annotations may behave incorrectly.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:41:12.066229Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:41:12.06626Z"}
